---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Lewiston Dispensary Guide | Maine Dispensary Guide" 
  description="Complete guide to opening a cannabis dispensary in Lewiston, Maine. Second-largest city market and opportunities."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1500916434205-0c77489c6cf7?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1200&h=400"
>
  <article>
    <div class="article-header">
      <h1>Lewiston Dispensary Guide</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">How to open a cannabis dispensary in Lewiston, Maine</p>
    </div>

    <Callout title="Strength in Heritage" type="tip">
      Lewiston's deep roots and industrial spirit make it a resilient and loyal market. By honoring the city's heritage while bringing a modern cannabis experience, you can build a business that truly belongs. It's all about community connection here!
    </Callout>

    <section>
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>Lewiston, Maine's second-largest city with 36,000+ residents, offers a solid market opportunity. Known for its Franco-American heritage and growing healthcare sector, Lewiston provides a stable customer base with more affordable costs than Portland. Before moving forward, familiarize yourself with the <a href="/guides/maine-cannabis-real-estate/">real estate requirements</a> essential for success.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Lewiston Market</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Factor</th><th>Assessment</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Population</td><td>36,000+</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Economy</td><td>Healthcare, retail, education</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Competition</td><td>Low</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Real Estate</td><td>Affordable ($12-18/sq ft)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Regulations</td><td>Standard state requirements</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Why Lewiston?</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Second Largest City</strong> - Significant population base</li>
        <li><strong>Low Competition</strong> - Opportunity to establish market presence</li>
        <li><strong>Affordable Costs</strong> - Much lower than Portland</li>
        <li><strong>Growing Area</strong> - Economic development ongoing</li>
        <li><strong>Regional Draw</strong> - Serves Androscoggin County</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Best Locations in Lewiston</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Center Street</strong> - Main downtown corridor</li>
        <li><strong>Mill Street</strong> - Historic downtown</li>
        <li><strong>Mount Auburn Avenue</strong> - Commercial area</li>
        <li><strong>Sabattus Street</strong> - Retail corridor</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Investment Requirements</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Category</th><th>Estimated Cost</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Real Estate (lease)</td><td>$2,000-3,500/mo</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Build-out</td><td>$100,000-180,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Total Investment</td><td>$350,000-650,000</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Target Market</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Local residents (medical and adult-use)</li>
        <li>Healthcare workers (Central Maine Medical Center)</li>
        <li>Bates College community</li>
        <li>Regional customers from surrounding towns</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="external-resources">
      <h2>Further Reading & Resources</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.lewistonmaine.gov/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">City of Lewiston Official Website</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    
    <section class="further-reading">
      <h2>Stay Ahead of the Curve</h2>
      <p>The cannabis landscape in Maine is constantly evolving. To ensure your business stays compliant and competitive, regularly consult the official resources provided by the <a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP)</a>. Their guidelines are the bedrock of a successful, long-term operation.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only and does not constitute legal or financial advice. Cannabis regulations are subject to change; always consult with the Maine Office of Cannabis Policy and qualified legal counsel.</em></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .article-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  section h2 { margin-top: 0; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0; }
  th, td { padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  th { background: var(--color-background); }
  ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .external-resources { margin-top: 3rem; padding-top: 2rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .further-reading { margin-top: 2rem; padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--color-surface); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 0.5rem; }
  .further-reading h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.5rem; }
  .further-reading p { margin-bottom: 0; }

  .external-resources ul { list-style: none; padding-left: 0; }
  .external-resources li { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .disclaimer { background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
</style>
